            "content": "Several factors influence the total cost of your commercial roof coating project:\n\nCoating System Selection: Acrylic systems cost 40-50% less than premium silicone but provide shorter lifespan. Silicone costs more initially but delivers 15-25 year performance versus 10-15 years for acrylic. Elastomeric falls between, offering flexibility at moderate cost.\n\nRoof Size & Complexity: Larger roofs (15,000+ square feet) achieve better per-square-foot pricing through economies of scale. Complex roofs with multiple penetrations, HVAC equipment, skylights, and level changes increase labor costs. Simple, open roofs with minimal penetrations cost less per square foot.\n\nSubstrate Condition: Roofs requiring extensive repairs before coating (seam failures, membrane damage, wet insulation removal) increase project costs. Well-maintained roofs with minimal repairs achieve lower total costs. Our pre-coating assessment identifies all repair work before providing firm pricing.\n\nSurface Preparation Requirements: Heavily soiled roofs require more intensive cleaning. Substrates needing primer (aged EPDM, smooth BUR) add material and labor costs. Metal roofs with rust require rust-inhibitive primer and treatment. Proper preparation is non-negotiable—we include all necessary prep work in our pricing.\n\nAccess & Logistics: Roof accessibility affects labor costs—easy access via stairs or exterior ladder reduces costs versus difficult access requiring lifts or special equipment. Occupied buildings requiring night/weekend work may incur scheduling premiums. Material staging areas and dumpster access affect logistics costs.\n\nWarranty Requirements: Extended manufacturer warranties (15-20 years) require specific coating thicknesses, often increasing material costs 15-25%. Standard 10-year warranties use manufacturer minimum specifications. We help you balance warranty length with budget.\n\nProject Timing: Off-season coating (October-March in Tucson) may offer better pricing due to lower demand. Summer coating works well when buildings are less occupied. We provide consistent pricing year-round but can sometimes offer flexibility for off-peak scheduling."
