            "type": "paragraph",
            "content": "The Compelling Economics of Roof Coating: Commercial roof coating delivers exceptional return on investment through three distinct value streams: deferred replacement costs, energy savings, and extended asset life. Consider a typical 15,000 square foot commercial building:\n\nWithout Coating (Replace at 15 years):\n- Original roof installation: $100,000 (year 0)\n- Replacement at 15 years: $110,000 (adjusted for inflation)\n- Total 30-year cost: $210,000\n- Cost per year: $7,000\n\nWith Coating (Coat at 12 years, replace at 27 years):\n- Original roof installation: $100,000 (year 0)\n- Coating at 12 years: $45,000\n- Replacement at 27 years: $125,000 (adjusted for inflation)\n- Total 30-year cost: $270,000\n- Cost per year: $9,000\n\nWait—coating appears more expensive? Not when you include energy savings and time-value of money:\n\nEnergy Savings Impact:\n- Annual cooling cost reduction: $8,500 (typical 20% savings)\n- 15-year energy savings: $127,500\n- Net 30-year cost with coating: $142,500\n- Net 30-year cost without coating: $210,000\n- Total savings: $67,500 over 30 years\n\nTime-Value Adjustment:\nDelaying $110,000 replacement by 12 years (year 15 → year 27) provides significant financial advantage. At 4% discount rate, the present value of year-27 replacement is $78,000 versus $101,000 for year-15 replacement—a $23,000 advantage beyond nominal savings."
